meshIneBits.config

Class PatternParameterConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • meshIneBits.config.PatternParameterConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PatternParameterConfig
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Describe a parameter, including uniqueName, title, description (further explain of use), default value (this currently accepts Double, List of Double) and step (minimal precision).

    These attributes minValue and maxValue define a range of selection.

    NHATHAN

    • Constructor Detail

      • PatternParameterConfig

        public PatternParameterConfig(java.lang.String uniqueName,
                              java.lang.String title,
                              java.lang.String description,
                              java.lang.Double minValue,
                              java.lang.Double maxValue,
                              java.lang.Object defaultValue,
                              java.lang.Double step)
        This will validate each input. If one does not satisfy, it will bring the default value. Be careful of List. Should use a real provided class implementing List, not by wrapping.
        Parameters:
        uniqueName - no constraint, but should be unique. Otherwise, it will crash preceding parameter with same uniqueName
        title - no constraint
        description - no constraint
        minValue - defines minimum of range of selection. Default = Double.MIN_VALUE
        maxValue - defines maximum of range of selection. Default = Double.MAX_VALUE
        defaultValue - should be either a Double or a List of Double.
        In case of a number: Default = 0.0 or minValue if inferior or maxValue if superior.
        In case of a list: an empty Vector of Double or a List of filtered Double
        step - must not be 0.0 or null or negative. Default = 1.0
